insects.origin: The citrus spiny whitefly has spread to multiple continents including Asia, Africa, Australia, America, Pacific Islands and Italy.
insects.identificationFeatures: Egg: The egg is minute (0.2 x 0.1 mm), yellow, stalked, curved and marked with polygonal areas (Quaintance 1903, Quaintance and Baker 1917).
insects.lifeCycle: The eggs are typically laid near each other on a food plants, such as citrus plants, usually on a leaf.
insects.pestControl: Biological control: Orange spiny whitefly outbreaks in other countries have been successfully brought under control through biological control.
